	(52,1,'2016-06-09 09:08:48','2016-06-09 09:08:48','[:sr]<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Rubrika Zentoteka integralni je deo Zent asopisa. Obzirom da e tampana tematska izdanja asopisa izlaziti dva puta godinje, rubrika je zamiljena kao prostor u okviru koga e se redovno objavljivati eseji, kritike, analize, prikazi, prevodi, intervjui, ali i proza, poezija, i vizuelni radovi.</span></p><p>Zentoteka je u stalnoj potrazi za objavljenim i neobjavljenim radovima iz domena drutvene teorije, politike, filozofije, arhitekture, tehnologije, kulture i umetnosti. Sve teme, ideje i oblici izraavanja su dobrodoli ukoliko su na liniji progresivnog kritinog promiljanja stvarnosti i ukoliko su situirani na bilo kojoj od mnotva instanci koje za okvir uzimaju ljudsku emancipaciju i tenju za izgradnjom slobodarskog, solidarnog i besklasnog drutva, ili ukratko Smrt Faizmu, Sloboda Narodu!</p><p>Zent ne veruje u objektivnost, neutralnost i apolitinost</p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Zent ne postavlja granice, ve ih ispituje</span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Zent je izvan anrovskih ogranienja i postojeih ureenja</span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Zent je za svakoga i za sve </span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Tekstovi pisani u esejistikog formi ne bi trebalo da sadre vie od 3000 rei, poeljno je takoe da imaju to manje fusnota i referenci. Tekstovi mogu biti napisani na srpsko-hrvatskom ili engleskom jeziku.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">aljite nam svoje tekstove, radove i/ili ideje na </span><a href=\"mailto:zentmagazine@gmail.com\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">zentmagazine@gmail.com</span></a></p><p>Radujemo se buduoj saradnji!</p><p>&nbsp;</p>[:en]<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Zentoteka is an integral part of Zent magazine. Given that the printed thematic issues of Zent will be published twice a year, Zentoteka is a dedicated space for regular publication of essays, analysis, translations, interviews, as well as prose, poetry, and visual artworks.</span></p><p>Zentoteka is constantly looking for both unpublished and published contributions from the fields of social theory, politics, philosophy, architecture, technology, culture and art. All topics, ideas and forms of expression are welcome in so far as they are in line with progressive critical reflection of reality and as they are situated in any of the multiple instances that take human emancipation and aspire to liberation, solidarity and a classless society as their starting point, or in short Death to fascism, freedom to the people!</p><p>Zent does not believe in objectivity, neutrality and apolitical stances</p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Zent does not set boundaries, but examines them</span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Zent is beyond genre limitations and currently-existing conventions</span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Zent is for everybody and for all</span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Texts written in essayistic form should not exceed 3000 words, they should also contain as few as possible footnotes and references. Texts can be submitted in Serbo-Croatian or English.</span></p><p>Send your essays, pieces and/or ideas at zentmagazine@gmail.com</p><p>We look forward to our future cooperation!</p>[:]','[:sr]Stalno otvoren poziv[:en]Submit to Zentotheque[:]','','publish','closed','closed','','stalno-otvoren-poziv','','','2016-07-12 13:27:27','2016-07-12 13:27:27','',0,'http://localhost/ZentZent/zent/app/?post_type=otvoreni_pozivi&#038;p=52',0,'otvoreni_pozivi','',0),
	(53,1,'2016-06-09 09:09:21','2016-06-09 09:09:21','[:sr]<p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Danas kada nam drava poruuje da smo lenji i da jo od malih nogu treba da se pripremamo za okrutno globalno trite u koje emo izgleda ve kao etvoronoci biti baeni, danas kada nam sa TV programa, fakultetskih govornica i stranica </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">lifestyle</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> magazina poruuju da ne moemo da radimo ako ne popravimo svoje ponaanje, ne promenimo svoje stavove i ne napunimo svoje CV-jeve neplaenim </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">internship-</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">ima, danas kada ne samo da moramo da radimo nego moramo i da volimo to to radimo, kada moramo da budemo nasmejani i veseli na svojim radnim mestima, danas kada je poslovni uspeh gotovo jedino merilo ostvarenosti, a neuspeh uvek i iskljuivo naa lina krivica, danas kada je obrazovanje svedeno na obuku za posao, kada je i slobodno vreme postalo produktivno, kada je meuljudska komunikacija komodifikovana, danas kada se ostaci kulta radnika nekadanje socijalne (socijalistike) drave transformiu u kult rada kao takvog, u pustinji post socijalizma, pitanja ta je to uopte rad, a ta je posao, kao i kako, zbog ega i pod kojim uslovima radimo, pitanja su koja stoje nad nama kao kakav dinovki neonski bilbord na vrhu stambenog solitera. Mi koji ivimo u tim soliterima, u stanovima svojih roditelja, u tuim stanovima koje sve tee sebi moemo da priutimo, u stanovima koje smo kupili na kredit i za koje sada robujemo nemilosrdnim bankama, mi za koje gubitak posla znai gubitak osnovnih uslova za ivot, se pitamo ta kog avola uopte moemo da (u)radimo?</span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">U sledeem broju Zenta, koji je posveen pitanju rada, elimo da ispitamo i analiziramo transformacije koje su dovele do sadanje opsednutosti radom i poslom, da problematizujemo koncepte i teorije, kao i da predloimo nove ideje i nova znaenja.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Zent ne veruje u nade novouspostavljene ideologije fleksibilnog, privremenog i projektnog rada koji nam navodno prua mogunost izbora. Ko je ikada bio samozaposlen zna da samozaposlenje vodi u samoeksploataciju - uvek vie a ipak uvek nedovoljno. Retki su srenici kojima ova praksa ne pada teko ali ne moemo svi biti programeri, a i neemo. Nametnut bestidnim ujedinjenjem drave i kapitala, neoliberalni projekat nam se predstavlja kao nova sloboda za pojedinca. Meutim, otvorena i prikrivena eksploatacija, postepeno sistematsko unitavanje poslednjih kolektivnih mehanizama sigurnosti i ljudske reprodukcije - od zdravstva, do stanovanja i obrazovanja, odnosno gotovo potpuno preputanje pojedinaca samima sebi koje je praeno rastuom zavisnou od linih veza, poznanstava i/ili platformski posredovane \'reputacije\', kao i nepromenjeni odnosi nejednakosti na radnom mestu i u drutvu i sve izrazitije ukidanje prava zaposlenih, druga su strana ovog sada ve izlizanog novia.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Sa druge strane, Zent ne veruje ni u jednostavan povratak na stabilna i sigurna radna mesta i kompromis pune zaposlenosti koji je udario temelje posleratnoj nacionalnoj dravi blagostanja ili socijalistikoj dravi u domaem kontekstu. Postojei parametri merenja drutvenog razvoja od BDP-a do prosene plate vie nam nita ne govore. U vremenu kada trina ekonomija proizvodi enormne koliine suvine populacije, kada iz sopstvene krize izlazi ne stvarajui obeana nova radna mesta, zaposleni su raspreni i neujedinjeni a nezaposleni saterani u sirotinjske kvartove i geta. Samoubistva radnika Foxconna i rapidno opadanje ivotnog standarda ak i za srednje klase globalnog Severa lokalne su manifestacije istog globalnog procesa - ultimativnog oslobaanja kapitala od radnika odnosno generisanje nepregledne armije rezervnog rada.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Pitanje ta je rad od posebnog je znaaja danas kada suoeni sa razvojem napredne robotike, koja bi uskoro mogla zameniti sav rutinski ali i veliki deo nerutinskog ljudskog rada, po prvi put moemo da mislimo redistribuciju drutvenog dobra na bazi univerzalnog osnovnog dohotka, time otvarajui vrata mogunosti organizacije drutva sa one strane rada. Rad kao smisao i svrha ljudi toliko je ukorenjen u nas da e se u susretu sa idejom njegove automizacije ljudi pitati: emu slue ljudi? Kojom etikom zameniti radnu etiku, ta postaje rad kada ne moramo vie da radimo da bismo preiveli, ili u mnogo gorem ali i mnogo izvesnijem scenariju kako preiveti kada posla (zaposlenja) vie nema? Brisanje granice izmeu rada i ivota, tj. izmeu radnog i slobodnog vremena ve je uveliko uzelo maha Pitanje kako oblikovati ovo sada jedinstveno vreme, odnosno spekulisanje o potencijalu budueg dobijenog vremena, o izgradnji drugaijeg drutva i ivota svakog pojedinca ini se kljunim. Moemo li jednostavno slediti naa slobodno izabrana zanimanja, opsesije, hobije i strasti, ili emo pak nastaviti u pravcu njihove apsolutne komodifikacije, u pravcu koji slobodno vreme pa ak i meuljudske odnose (druenje) pretvara u potencijalnu monetarnu vrednost.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Zent veruje u mogunosti povratka na pokuaje izgradnje solidarnog i besklasnog drutva, kroz afirmaciju njihovih egalitarnih dosega, na nain da taj povratak razume kao nastavak rada i borbe, </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">update</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, i ponovno reformulisanje egalitarnog drutva. Zent vas poziva da spekuliete o ovom potencijalnom prostoru slobode od posla ili pak obrnuto borbe protiv invazije posla u slobodno vreme, kao i novim pitanjima vezanim za drugaije organizovanje drutva bez rada. Kako emo deliti ono preostalo obaveznog rada u novom drutvu? ta postaje odgovornost? Napomene da nije mogue sav rad automatizovati, od uvanja dece i brige za starima, do novih obaveza unutar zajednice, zahtevaju i nove odgovornosti i obaveze svakoga od nas. Na kraju moemo se zapitati i ta je danas rad (ukoliko uopte postoji) koji nije podvrgnut trinoj razmeni, ta je rad jedne umetnice/umetnika, pesnikinje/pesnika, filozofkinje/filozofa, naunice/naunika, ta je angaovani rad, entuzijazam i odakle dolazi volja i elja za njim.</span></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\"><strong>Praktine smernice</strong></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Svi oblici izraavanja su dobrodoli - arhitektonski projekti, radovi iz oblasti prirodnih i drutvenih nauka, tehnologije, stripovi, ilustracije, intervjui, fotografije, istraivanja, vizuelni radovi, radovi umetnika i radovi radnika, poezija, proza, kao i teorijski i esejistiki tekstovi. Tekstovi pisani u esejistikog formi ne bi trebalo da sadre vie od 3000 rei, a poeljno je takoe da imaju to manje fusnota i referenci. Tekstovi mogu biti napisani na srpsko-hrvatskom ili engleskom jeziku.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Rok za podnoenje predloga je 15.08.2016.Izabrani autori/ke e biti pozvani da svoje gotove tekstove/radove dostave do 01.10.2016. Svoje predloge aljite na </span><a href=\"mailto:zentmagazine@gmail.com\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">zentmagazine@gmail.com</span></a></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Radujemo se buduoj saradnji!</span></p>[:en]<p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 20px;\">Today when the State itself is telling us that we are lazy and that we should as early as children be prepared to be thrown into the cruel global market, today when everything from TV programmes and lifestyle magazines to university professors instructs us that we cant work unless we adjust our behaviour, change our attitudes and fill-up our CVs with unpaid internships, today when we are not only obliged to work but should also love it, when we must be cheerful and happy at our workplaces, today when commercial success is the only measure of achievement and failure to succeed exclusively our own fault, today when education is reduced to job training, when leisure has become productive, when human relation and interaction has been commodified, today when the leftovers of the workers cult of the former social (socialist) state are increasingly transformed into the cult of work as such, in this post-socialist desert, the question what is work, and what is labour, as well as how, why and under what conditions we work, stands above us like some sort of giant neon billboard standing on top of a residential building. We who live in these buildings, in our parents apartments, renting someone else\'s apartments that we can no longer afford, in apartments we paid with debt for, we for whom the loss of a job means the loss of basic means for survival, wonder what the hell can we at all do?</span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 20px;\">In the next issue of Zent dedicated to the question of work, we wish to explore, investigate and analyze the transformations that brought about the contemporary obsession with work, to question concepts and theories and to suggest new ideas and new meanings.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 20px;\">Zent does not believe in the hopes of newly established ideology of flexible, temporary and project-driven work which supposedly offers numerous choices. Anyone whos ever been self-employed knows that self-employment leads to self-exploitation - ever more but never enough. Rare are those whom this does not pose a great burden, but we cannot all become developers, and we dont want to. Imposed by the shameless union between capital and the state, this neoliberal project is being represented as the new freedom for the individual. However, open and disguised exploitation, gradual systematic destruction of collective mechanisms that previously facilitated human reproduction - from health to housing and education, i.e. the imperative of individual self-sufficiency which is accompanied by the increasing dependency on personal connections, contacts and networks as well as platform-facilitated reputation, together with the unchanged relationships of inequality in the working place and in society and the pronounced suppression of workers rights, represent the other side of this now already worn-out coin.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 20px;\">On the other hand, Zent does not believe in the simple return to stable and secure working positions and the compromise of full employment that laid the foundation of the post-war national welfare or socialist state. Existing parameters measuring social development from GDP to average salary do not tell us anything no more. In the time when market economy is producing enormous quantities of surplus populations, when its coming out of its crisis without producing the promised new jobs, the employed are dispersed and scattered and the unemployed pushed aside, herded into urban slams and ghettos. The suicides of Foxconn workers and rapidly declining living standards even for the middle classes of the global North represent local manifestations of the same global process - the capitals ultimate disposal of workers, or put differently the hyperproduction of an endless reserve army of labor. </span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 20px;\">The questions pertaining to the issue of work are especially important today when faced with the development of advanced robotics that could shortly replace all routine and even most of non-routine human labour, for the first allows us to think redistribution of social wealth on the basis of universal basic income, thereby opening up the possibility of contemplating the organization of society beyond work. Work as something which gives meaning and purpose is rooted in us to the extent that faced with its automation people are ought to wonder: What are we for? By which ethics we are to replace the working ethics, what does work become when we are no longer obliged to work in order to survive, or in much worse but much more convincing scenario - how to survive when work i.e. jobs are no longer available? The fading of difference between work and life, or more precisely between work and leisure has already taken place Speculations on how to shape this now singular time, i.e. on the potential of this future time liberated from work, about the possibility to build a different society and different life of each individual, seem to be crucial. Could we simply follow our freely chosen interest, professions and obsessions, hobbies and passions, or will we rather continue in the direction of their absolute commodification, in the direction that transforms leisure and even interpersonal relations into potential sources of income? </span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 20px;\">Zent believes in the possibility of returning to the attempts of building a solidary and classless society through the affirmation of their egalitarian principles, whereas this return is understood as continuation of work and struggle, an update and re-formulation of the idea of an egalitarian society. Zent invites you to speculate about the potential of life liberated from work or the other way around, about the struggle against the invasion of work into leisure and life, as well as about new questions related to organization of society without work. How to divide amongst ourselves the obligatory work that remains? What does responsibility become? Remarks that not all work can be automated, from care work to new obligations within a community, demand new responsibilities and duties that each of us must take on. In the end, we may also wonder, what is work today (if it exists at all) that is not subjected to market exchange, what is the work of an artist, poet, philosopher, scientist, what is engaged work, enthusiasm and where does the will and desire for it come from?</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Practical Guidelines</span></strong></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">All forms of expression and approaches are welcome - architectural projects, natural and social sciences, technology, comics, illustrations, interviews, photography, research findings, visual and artistic interventions, works of art and works of workers, poetry, prose, as well as theoretical and essayistic formats. Texts written in essayistic form should not exceed 3000 words, they should also contain as few as possible footnotes and references. Texts can be submitted in Serbo-Croatian or English.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Proposals should be submitted by August 15 2016. Selected authors will be invited to submit their full texts/pieces by October 10 2016. Send your proposals to </span><a href=\"mailto:zentmagazine@gmail.com\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">zentmagazine@gmail.com</span></a></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">We look forward to our future cooperation!</span></p>[:]','[:sr]ZENT #02 Rad - Otvoren poziv[:en]ZENT #02 Work - Open Call[:]','','publish','closed','closed','','zent-02-rad-otvoren-poziv','','','2016-07-12 13:27:47','2016-07-12 13:27:47','',0,'http://localhost/ZentZent/zent/app/?post_type=otvoreni_pozivi&#038;p=53',0,'otvoreni_pozivi','',0),
