	(258,1,'2016-07-05 20:32:51','2016-07-05 20:32:51','[:sr]<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 16px;\">Zent opstaje zahvaljujui velikodunosti, solidarnosti i podrci svojih italaca. Ako moe pretplati se, porui, ili doniraj. </span></p><p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Zentu cilj nije profit ve pristupano znanje za sve. Zent je utemeljen u vrednostima zajednitva ali i uverenju da drava i dravljanstvo nisu njegov nuni medijator. Zent shvata zajednitvo kao prvi od preduslova za ostvarivanje izvan-rednog mesta za sve.</span></p><p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Svojom donacijom podraete tampana i online izdanja asopisa, odravanje javnih razgovora i predavanja kao i rad kritiara/ki, teoretiara/ki, umetnika/ca, pisaca i spisateljica.</span></p><p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><br /><br /></p>[:en]<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 16px;\">Zent survives thanks to the generosity, solidarity and support of its readers. If you can please subscribe, purchase, or donate.</span></p><p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Zent does not strive to profit but to offer accessible knowledge for all. Zent is grounded in the values of the common and the conviction that neither the state nor citizenship are its necessary mediators. Zent understands the existence of the common as the first prerequisite for achieving an extra-ordinary place for all.</span></p><p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">With your donation you will support print and online editions of the magazine, organization of public discussions and lectures, as well as the work of independent authors: critics, theorists, artist, and writers.</span></p>[:]','Podri','','inherit','closed','closed','','37-revision-v1','','','2016-07-05 20:32:51','2016-07-05 20:32:51','',37,'http://zentmagazine.com/test/37-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(259,1,'2016-07-05 20:44:23','2016-07-05 20:44:23','[:sr]<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 20px;\">Zent je asopis za izvan-redno promiljanje sadanjosti.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Zent je prekaran  neizvestan, rizian, nepredvidljiv. U isto vreme ugroen i nesiguran u samoga sebe. Intutivan pre nego programiran, nasumian pre nego usidren, mesto za misao, praksu i izraz. Zent je forma anksioznosti, aktivna, svesna izmetenost.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">U argonu (srpsko-hrvatskog jezika) zentati se podrazumeva odreeni nivo straha (od) i anksioznosti (prema). Upravo zbog toga Zent je mesto prelaznosti i podvoenja: umesto beanja i negiranja, Zent iskoriava Strah. Zentati se znai iekivati (nita odreeno), biti izvan reda i izvan mesta, neprestano u ruevinama, na niijoj zemlji, nikada tamo gde te se oekuje. Jer da bi se uzdrmao postojei poredak potrebno je sakupiti zajednike snage, odupreti se svakom pokuaju aproprijacije, naturalizacije i normalizacije.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Zent je prostor za artikulisano politiko miljenje koje nije demagoko, konformistiko i banalno. Ipak, Zent je mesto i za spontanost, patetiku i greku. Zent je politian utoliko to politiku ne vidi samo kao pitanje institucija ve pre svega kao pitanje svakodnevnog odnosa pojedinaca i zajednica jednih prema drugima i prema svetu. Zent je (samo)kritian i polemian. Zent postoji u formi tematskih tampanih izdanja i online asopisa koji redovno objavljuje eseje, intervjue, recenzije, poeziju, prozu i vizualne radove. Zent pie smelim, pristupanim jezikom i eksperimentie sa formama izraza, sa namerom da problematizuje odnos izmeu visoke, narodne i popularne kulture, eksperata i amatera, upravitelja i onih kojima se upravlja.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Tekstove objavljene na Zentu moete slobodno kopirati i prenositi uz obavezno jasno istaknuto ime autora/ke i izvor lanka kao i uz uslov da ga potom sami ne zatiujete autorskim pravom.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p>[:en]<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 20px;\">Zent is a magazine for extra-ordinary reflections on the present.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Zent is a precarious  uncertain, risky, unpredictable. Both unsafe and insecure. Intuitive rather than programmed, adrift rather than anchored, a place for thought, practice and expression. Zent is a form of anxiety. An active, conscious displacement.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">In vernacular Serbo-Croatian language to zent implies a certain degree of fear (from) and anxiety (for). Precisely because of that Zent is a transitive and subsuming place: instead of fleeing and negating, Zent exploits the fear. To zent is to anticipate (nothing in particular), to be out-of- order and out-of-place, constantly in ruins, in no mans land, never there where you are expected. For to shake established orders is to accumulate collective strengths, resisting any attempts at appropriation, naturalization and normalization.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Zent is a place for articulated political opinion that is not conformist and banal. However, Zent is also a space for spontaneity, pathos and mistakes. Zent is political, insofar as it doesnt see politics only as an institutional matter, but rather as a question of everyday relationships of individuals and communities between each other and the world. Zent is (self)critical and polemical. Zent takes the form of periodical tematic printed editions and online magazine that regularly publishes essays, interviews, reviews, poetry, fiction and visual works. Zent writes in bold, accessible language and experiments with the forms of expression, with intention to question the relationship between high, folk and popular culture, experts and amateurs, governors and those who are to be governed.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Articles published on Zent can be freely copied and shared but with clearly stated name of the author and source of the article as well as under the condition that you do not protect the article with copyright.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p>[:]','[:sr]O nama[:en]About Us[:]','','inherit','closed','closed','','28-revision-v1','','','2016-07-05 20:44:23','2016-07-05 20:44:23','',28,'http://zentmagazine.com/test/28-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
